{{Unlicensed}}'''The Fatal Visionaries''' were a group of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] formed by [[Zhen Mirat]]. They were known to be ruthless cutthroats, often looting and destroying cargo [[Starship/Legends|ships]]. It was known that they had did this to at least two bulk [[Freighter/Legends|freighters]] belonging to the [[Corporate Sector Authority/Legends|Corporate Sector Authority]], four [[Light freighter/Legends|light freighters]] belonging to independent operators, as well as three confirmed, and four unconfirmed, [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] cargo ships.

Members of the group included Mirat, the leader, [[Chanchaz Iryt]] and [[Huggtar]], the muscle, [[Vazan Felix]], a free-trader forced to co-operate by piloting his ship, and [[X (droid)|X]], an [[Assassin droid/Legends|assassin droid]]. They operated from the [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] [[KS-500 Spaceways Transport light freighter]] ''[[The Fatal Vision]]'' which had once been Vazan's ship under the name ''Tine's Future''. At some point in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], they were assessed by [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Herrit]] of [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] who reported to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and reached a consensus that they could be utilized to great effect by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]]. They were offered restricted technology in exchange for only attacking rebel and [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] ships, although they were still allowed to attack the rare free-trader ship with no consequences. Later in the war, Vazan approached the rebels for help in finding and freeing his family. The chain of events which occurred due to this caused a group of rebels to eventually kill every member of the Visionaries save Huggtar, who was recruited into the Rebellion as a medic.

